ve tax breaks to help families with child care
 or retirement.&nbsp; And if we did these things, then we&#8217;d help to r=
estore the sense that hard work is rewarded and we could build an economy t=
hat truly works for everybody.&nbsp; (Applause.)&nbsp;
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Ca=
libri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"text-indent:.5in"><span style=3D"font-size:=
11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Now, the reason some of =
these things have not happened, even though the majority of people approve =
of them, is really simple. It's not because I wasn&#8217;t
 proposing them.&nbsp; It wasn&#8217;t because the facts and the evidence s=
howed they wouldn't work.&nbsp; It was because a huge chunk of Americans, e=
specially young people, do not vote.&nbsp;
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal" style=3D"text-indent:.5in"><span style=3D"font-size:=
11.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">In 2014, voter turnout w=
